    "source_sections": {
      "references": "",
      "remarks": "A conjecture of Erd\\H{o}s and S\\'{a}rk\\\"{o}zy. Some condition relating $A$ and $B$ is necessary since, for example, if $A$ is the set of all integers with only even binary digits and $B$ is the set of all integers with only odd binary digits then $1_A\\ast 1_B(n)=1$ for all $n$.\n\nThis is a stronger form of [28]. See also [331]."
    },
